$ Graphviz: attribute type: escString
@ escString

`escString` is the → tools/Graphviz/attributes/types[type] of the following → tools/Graphviz/attributes[attributes]:
  • `URL`
  • `edgeURL`
  • `edgehref`
  • `edgetarget`
  • `edgetooltip`
  • `headURL`
  • `headref`
  • `headtarget`
  • `headtooltip`
  • `href`
  • `id`
  • `labelURL`
  • `labelhref`
  • `labeltarget`
  • `labeltooltip`

Because the → tools/Graphviz/attributes/types/lblString[`lblString` type] can be an `escString`, the specifica of `escString` are also applicable to the following attributes (if they're not used as *HTML like labels*):
  • `headlabel`
  • `label`
  • `taillabel`
  • `xlabel`

In an *escString*, some escape sequences are replaced:
  • `\G` with the name of the graph or the name of a cluster
  • `\N` with the name of the node
  • `\H` the name of the head node in an edge
  • `\T` the name of the tail node in an edge

gh|about-Graphviz|/labels/escString.dot||
gh|about-Graphviz|/labels/img/escString.png||

The default value of a → tools/Graphviz/elems/node[node's] → tools/Graphviz/attributes/label[`label` attribute] is `\N`.

sa:

  The → tools/Graphviz/attributes/types/lblString[`lblString` type]

  → tools/Graphviz/attributes/types
